 the edge length of the box is denoted as $a$, then the volume of the box is $a^3$, and the volume of the sphere is $\\frac{4}{3} \\pi \\left(\\frac{a}{2}\\right)^3 = \\frac{\\pi a^3}{6}$, so the volume not occupied by the sphere is $a^3 - \\frac{\\pi a^3}{6} = a^3 \\left(1 - \\frac{\\pi}{6}\\right)$</think> <answer> $27000 - 4500\\pi$\\end{document} To solve the problem, we can first determine the volume of the box and the volume of the sphere. Then, we can find the volume of the box that is not occupied by the sphere.\n\n1. The volume of the box, which is a cube with edge length 30 cm, is calculated as follows:\n\\[ \\text{Volume of the box} = 30^3 = 27000 \\text{cm}^3 \\]\n\n2. The diameter of the sphere is equal to the edge length of the box, so the diameter of the sphere is 30 cm. Therefore, the radius of the sphere is:\n\\[ \\text{Radius of the sphere} = \\frac{30}{2} = 15 \\text{cm} \\]\nThe volume of the sphere is calculated as follows:\n\\[ \\text{Volume of the sphere} = \\frac{4}{3} \\pi \\left(15\\right)^3 = \\frac{4}{3} \\pi \\times 3375 = 4500\\pi \\text{cm}^3 \\]\n\n3. The volume of the box that is not occupied by the sphere is:\n\\[ \\text{Volume not occupied by the sphere} = \\text{Volume of the box} - \\text{Volume of the sphere} = 27000 - 4500\\pi \\text{cm}^3 \\]\n\nSo, the final answer is:\n\\[ \\boxed{27000 - 4500\\pi} \\]\n\nHere is the Python code for verification:\n\n```python\n# Define the edge length of the cube (box)\na = 30\n\n# Calculate the volume of the box\nvolume_box = a ** 3\n\n# Calculate the radius of the sphere\nradius_sphere = a / 2\n\n# Calculate the volume of the sphere\nvolume_sphere = (4 / 3) * 3.14159 * (radius_sphere ** 3)\n\n# Calculate the volume not occupied by the sphere\nvolume_not_occupied = volume_box - volume_sphere\n\n# Display the final result\nprint(volume_not_occupied)\n```", "truth": "27000-4500\\pi", "reward_format": 0.0, "reward_answer": 0.0, "reward_total": 0.0}, {"prompt": "A conversation between User and 